------------------------------LORA TRIGGERS ARE SETTED UP AUTOMATICALLY IN THE PREPROCESS DATA, DON'T INCLUDE IT IN YOUR DATASET------------------------------------------------------
QWEN OMNI 2.5 it's a heavy, not because its model size, but for the large context window needed and trying to adjust lower amount of tokens can return precisition error, so it is only recomended for Big Gpus (apart of this, it fails sometimes without transicribing correctly running in 8 bits) Qwen omni can also detect sounds effect, but as i said is heavy and sometimes not precise. Because this, i setted up Qwen3 VL 2B instruct + Qwen3 transcribe and it does the job so weel and 100x faster, with more rich descriptions and also it transcribe perfectly and safe to classify by node all sections of the json. Also i setted up it to pass automatically the json file into the data foler and the trigger node. All the process is automatic you just need to set up the Directory of your videos/imagesSequence.
Important to check your Json dataset:
You can also create, retouch manually if you desire (even you can create a separated workflow easily making a copy the Qwen3 subgraph), the JSON structure is like this (where subsequent captions are separated by comas "," :

GENERATED WITHOUT AUDIO [video or sequential images]:
[
  {
    "caption": "[VISUAL]: A person sitting on an ornate, dark gray throne. The throne has intricate carvings and scroll-like armrests. The person is wearing a black outfit with gold accents. The top is a revealing, corset-like design with orange and gold elements, and a skull pendant. They also have black gloves with gold details and black boots. The person is wearing a black mask with gold and red accents, and has horns protruding from the top of the mask. The background is completely black, which makes the figure and the throne stand out. The person's hands are resting on the armrests of the throne, and they are looking straight ahead.\n\n[TEXT]: None",
    "media_path": "ComfyUI_00208_.png"
  }

]
GENERATED WITH AUDIO:
[
  {
    "caption": "[VISUAL]: A man is sitting in a car, wearing a black hat and a black suit with a white shirt and black tie. He appears to be in a state of distress or panic, with his mouth open and eyes wide. In the background, another person is visible, but they are out of focus and not the main focus of the scene. The setting seems to be inside a car, as indicated by the car interior elements like the window and seatbelt. The lighting is dim, suggesting it might be nighttime or the car's interior is not well-lit.\n\n[SPEECH]: \"Está nerviosa por el vuelo.\"\n\n[TEXT]: None\n\n[SOUNDS]: None",
    "media_path": "man_in_car.mp4",
    "reference_path" : optional for control depth, canny, pose, etc.. Added automatically activating reference video toggle in Qwen3 subgraph. (you just need to pass the path in the begining
  }
]

For the moment video reference is not added automatically if you use video to video mode.
